    <h2 id="whyIs">Why is watering important?</h2>
    
    <p><br>
      <ls>
        <li>Watering a plant is very important for its growth. Plants use a process called photosynthesis to create energy and water is required for it to work. Photosynthesis uses carbon dioxide from the air and hydrogen from the water to create a type of sugar that can be used by the plant to grow. </li>
        <br>
        <li>Water carries nutrients like the sugar from the leaves to the stems and buds, supporting new growth.</li>
        <br>
        <li>Water helps the plant stay cool by evaporating water in the leaves and taking away excess heat, this also pulls up more water from the ground.</li>
        <br>
        <li>Water provides support to the plant cells and allows it to bend in the wind without breaking.</li>
        <br>
        <li>Underwatered plants are suseptible to pests. </li>
      </ls>
  
