    <h2 id="howTo">Proper Watering Techniques</h2>
    <br>
    <p>Water in the evening or early morning, watering while the soil is cool lets the plant absorb more of the moisture before it evaporates. When you water, keep your plant leaves dry, this helps avoid various diseases. Water evenly and gradually. Make sure that the plant is getting an even amount of water from all sides, this helps promote even root growth. Watering gradually allows time for the water to seep into the soil and avoids runoff, try watering in parts. Water needs to get to the plant roots to be effective. Watering deeply less frequently is preferable to watering lightly everyday. Avoid overwatering, if too much water is left in the soil it can drown the roots of the plant. Make sure your plants have good drainage so the roots can breathe.</p>
